&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Formally deputise for the SMF17 (MLRO), assisting in the second-line oversight of Raisin UK’s financial crime prevention strategy and regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the MLRO in developing, maintaining, and regularly reviewing the firm’s AML/CTF policies, procedures, and risk assessments to align with evolving regulatory standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a subject matter expert for internal teams, providing clear compliance guidance on onboarding, product developments, and external queries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, perform, and maintain robust second-line controls and monitoring processes - including testing the effectiveness of financial crime systems and settings, identifying gaps, and driving framework improvements based on the results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the investigation of internal unusual activity reports, ensuring prompt resolution, and manage the drafting and submission of Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct AML/CFT horizon scanning and reporting to relevant stakeholders including senior management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide oversight and subject matter expertise in responding to financial crime related queries from partners or our service bank, ensuring responses align with regulatory expectations and internal policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the Compliance function in internal governance forums e.g. Risk Committee.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with regulatory reporting processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support on regulatory compliance topics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a proven track record in financial crime compliance within UK financial services (FinTech, retail banking, or payments preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are likely a Senior Financial Crime Manager looking for your first formal step up. In particular, you will have: Deep, practical understanding of the UK financial crime landscape, including the FCA Handbook, UK Money Laundering Regulations (MLRs), JMLSG guidance, and POCA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience overseeing controls testing, managing financial crime escalations, and leading the drafting a

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;sc-gEkIjz cjtSrT MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-body1 sc-hoLEA&quot;&gt;Raisin is the world’s leading platform for savings and investment products. Founded in 2012, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;FinTech&lt;/strong&gt; connects consumers with banks in the EU, the UK and the US. This gives consumers &lt;strong&gt;better interest rates&lt;/strong&gt; and banks a &lt;strong&gt;diversified form of refinancing&lt;/strong&gt;. Our vision is to offer savings and investments without barriers and thus open up the global 160 trillion euro market.&lt;/p&gt;
