&lt;li&gt;A degree in economics, finance, mathematics, or the natural sciences is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, you have a degree in another subject (including business) and are committed to skeptical empiricism, both in investments and in business more broadly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You trust your judgment and can work independently. You feel comfortable taking risk-based decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are precise in your language.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a sense of humor and don’t take yourself too seriously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You care about both processes and results, but much more about results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to programming languages and basic software development workflows is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with pension products is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
